## Core Proposition
In non-destructive testing (NDT), a measurement is not validated by its conformity to an idealized blueprint; it is validated solely by its **repeatability**. If a structural test cannot be repeated with identical parameters to yield the identical structural signature, the test is invalid. The material is not known. 

When this principle is applied to the architecture of mind and mathematics, "truth" ceases to be a static noun or a representation to be chased. Truth is a **string verb**—the continuous, unbroken operation of a system that matches its pre-positioned awareness to the physical terrain cleanly, perfectly, and repeatedly without destroying the container[span_0](start_span)[span_0](end_span)[span_1](start_span)[span_1](end_span). 

If the operator model relies on a static, flat interpretation of truth that results in an open load error ($\pi = \text{OL}$), a non-destructive framework demands a repeatable loop that closes the circuit[span_2](start_span)[span_2](end_span).

